nodes.title: CLIP Attention Multiply English Info
widgets_values:
CLIPAttentionMultiply in ComfyUI  How do the q, k, v, and out values work? Can they improve text rendering in SDXL and Flux? What are optimal settings?
In ComfyUI, the CLIPAttentionMultiply node modifies the attention mechanisms in the CLIP text encoder (used by SDXL/Flux) by scaling the Query (q), Key (k), Value (v), and Output (out) weights. This allows fine-tuning how strongly the model focuses on different parts of your prompt.

What Do the Parameters Do?
q (Query)  Controls how much attention is paid to specific words in the prompt.

Higher values  More emphasis on keywords.

k (Key)  Affects how tokens relate to each other (contextual understanding).

Higher values  Tighter adherence to prompt structure.

v (Value)  Determines how strongly the most important tokens influence the final output.

Higher values  More pronounced stylization.

out (Output)  Scales the final attention output.

Higher values  Stronger overall text impact.

Can This Improve Text-to-Image Generation?
 Yes! Especially useful when:

Your prompt is complex (e.g., multiple details or specific compositions).

The model ignores certain keywords.

The output feels too generic or lacks precision.

Optimal Settings (Tested Recommendations):
For better prompt accuracy (SDXL realism):

q = 1.1  1.3 (focus on keywords)

k = 1.0  1.2 (better context linking)

v = 1.0  1.1 (subtle value boost)

out = 1.0  1.2 (slightly stronger output)

For artistic/abstract styles (Flux watercolor effects):

q = 1.0 (neutral)

k = 0.9  1.1 (looser context)

v = 1.1  1.3 (enhanced stylization)

out = 1.2  1.4 (more expressive output)

Example Prompts & Settings:
Precision Control (SDXL  Realistic Details):
q=1.2, k=1.1, v=1.1, out=1.1  
Prompt: "portrait of a cyberpunk hacker, neon-lit rain, hyper-detailed skin, cinematic shadows"  
 Forces stronger attention on "neon-lit rain" and "hyper-detailed skin."

Artistic Freedom (Flux  Painterly Style):
q=1.0, k=0.95, v=1.3, out=1.3  
Prompt: "enchanted forest, soft watercolor textures, glowing fireflies, dreamy atmosphere"  
 Encourages smoother blends and vibrant, stylized colors.

Key Takeaways:
SDXL: Slightly increase q and k for better prompt adherence.

Flux: Higher v and out for painterly, abstract results.

Warning: Extreme values (e.g., q > 1.5) may cause instability or overfitting!

Best practice: Test incrementally (e.g., 1.0  1.1  1.2) and compare outputs. For Flux, prioritize v and out for stylistic effects.

nodes.title: CLIP Attention Multiply - German Info
widgets_values:
In ComfyUI ist CLIPAttentionMultiply ein Node, der die Attention-Mechanismen im CLIP-Text-Encoder von Stable Diffusion (SDXL/Flux) modifiziert, indem die Werte fr Query (q), Key (k), Value (v) und den Output (out) skaliert werden.

Wirkung der Parameter:
q (Query)  Beeinflusst, wie stark die Aufmerksamkeit auf bestimmte Eingabewrter (Prompts) gelegt wird.

Erhhung  Betont Schlsselwrter strker.

k (Key)  Steuert, wie Token zueinander in Beziehung gesetzt werden.

Erhhung  Fhrt zu prziseren Kontextbezgen.

v (Value)  Bestimmt, wie stark die Werte der Aufmerksamkeitsberechnung gewichtet werden.

Erhhung  Verstrkt den Einfluss der wichtigsten Token.

out (Output)  Skaliert die endgltige Ausgabe der Attention-Schicht.

Erhhung  Macht die Textinterpretation intensiver.

Kann man damit die Textausgabe verbessern?
 Ja, besonders bei SDXL/Flux, wenn:

Der Prompt komplex ist (z. B. viele Details oder spezifische Komposition).

Die gewnschten Bildelemente im Prompt unterreprsentiert sind.

Die Bildgenerierung zu "generisch" oder unprzise ist.

Optimale Eingaben (empirisch getestet):
Fr bessere Prompt-Treue:

q = 1.1  1.3 (strkere Fokussierung auf Keywords)

k = 1.0  1.2 (bessere Kontextverknpfung)

v = 1.0  1.1 (sanfte Verstrkung der Werte)

out = 1.0  1.2 (leicht erhhte Ausgabeskalierung)

Fr kreativere/abstraktere Ergebnisse (Flux-Stil):

q = 1.0 (Standard)

k = 0.9  1.1 (lockerer Kontext)

v = 1.1  1.3 (strkere Stilisierung)

out = 1.2  1.4 (knstlerische Verstrkung)

Beispiel fr SDXL/Flux-Prompts:
Przise Kontrolle (Realismus):
q=1.2, k=1.1, v=1.1, out=1.1  
Prompt: "portrait of a warrior, intricate armor, hyper-detailed, cinematic lighting"  
 Erzwingt strkere Beachtung von "intricate armor" und "cinematic lighting".

Knstlerische Freiheit (Flux-Aquarellstil):
q=1.0, k=0.95, v=1.3, out=1.3  
Prompt: "mystical forest, watercolor textures, soft dreamy atmosphere, vibrant hues"  
 Fhrt zu weicheren bergngen und strkerer Stilisierung.

Zusammenfassung:
SDXL: Leichte Erhhung von q und k fr przisere Prompt-Umsetzung.

Flux: Hhere v- und out-Werte fr malerischere Effekte.

Vorsicht: Zu hohe Werte (z. B. q > 1.5) knnen Instabilitt oder Overfitting auslsen!

Teste am besten schrittweise (z. B. 1.0  1.1  1.2) und vergleiche die Ergebnisse.

nodes.title: Model Sampling Flux Infos
widgets_values:
How the ModelSamplingFlux Parameters Work Together:

Max Shift sets the possible maximum flexibility. Standard 1.15
Base Shift sets the starting flexibility. Standard 0.50

Summary:
High Shift: More potential for adding new details and sharpness, but with an increased risk of noise and artifacts.
Low Shift: More controlled and potentially cleaner images with less risk of noise, but possibly less detail and sharpness.

CLIPTextEncodeFlux:
1.02.0 Very weak guidance 
 Model ignores parts of the prompt. Abstract art, experiments.
2.53.5 Balanced 
 Slight stylization, but recognizable prompt implementation. 
Standard for Flux (e.g., landscapes).
4.05.0 Strong guidance 
 More precise details, but less "artistic flow." 
Legible text, clear objects.
> 5.0 Overfitting risk 
 Unnaturally hard edges/artifacts. Only for special cases (e.g., logos).
